& [CurrentAttentionRuntimeRegistryState] is the live semantic registry for active attention
  + [registry_status] is active
  + [registry_scope] is pressure impact ThinkAbout pilot candidate inspection
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_pressure_impact_pilot_candidate
  + [active_frame_count] is 1
  + [suspended_frame_count] is 0
  + [closed_frame_count] is 9
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [registry_outside] is hidden activations, exact transformer attention, model weights, worker mutation authority, broad task competence, copy-exact overclaim, and unrelated Pinky worktree changes

  = must: update this state when focus materially changes
  = must: preserve return anchors before closing or suspending frames
  = must: keep the registry semantic and visible, not native-runtime or hidden-state based
  = should: stay compact enough for context-compression re-entry

& [AttentionFrame_2026_06_24_PressureImpactPilotCandidate] is the active semantic stack frame for inspecting the first synthesis-backed LM Studio worker pilot candidate
  + [frame_id] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_pressure_impact_pilot_candidate
  + [frame_state] is active
  + [parent_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_lmstudio_worker_pilot_queue
  + [child_frame_set] is functional_lmstudio_lane, readiness_synthesis, one_minute_heartbeat, operating_loop_tick_015, task_frame_launch_queue, pressure_impact_thinkabout_016, latch_set, outside_boundary, commit_receipt
  + [return_anchor] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\state\CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [frame_trace] is lmstudio_limited_worker_pilot_queue_001.sop, pressure_impact_thinkabout_prompt_016.sop, lm_studio_worker_readiness_synthesis_20260624_016.sop, 2026-06-24_operating_loop_tick_015.sop, and CurrentFocalPoint.sop
  + [focus_register] is inspect pressure_impact_thinkabout_016 before any launch
  + [question_register] is whether the candidate gates, prompt packet, capture target, validator, and outside boundary are sufficient to run
  + [delineation_register] is inside queue readiness, prompt packet, launch command, capture target, required fields, required terms, forbidden terms, and synthesis latch set
  + [periphery_register] is worker launch outside until chosen, broad competence outside, project-root authority outside, worker mutation outside, direct trust outside, automatic launch outside, and unrelated dirty files outside
  + [operation_register] is inspect_candidate, decide_launch_or_adjust, preserve_raw_output_if_launched, validate_result, record_review, emit_next_tick
  + [evidence_register] is pilot queue record, prompt packet, readiness synthesis, and operating_loop_tick_015
  + [wisdom_register] is the pilot is useful because it tests real SOP proposal value on pressure and impact signals without granting authority
  + [caution_register] is no launch occurs merely from queue readiness and any worker output remains not integrated until Codex review
  + [balance_register] is stable because queue compilation is complete and launch remains a separate decision
  + [integration_register] is pilot queue compiled, worker launch pending inspection
  + [frame_outside] is hidden model state, worker file mutation, remote claims before push, broad local-worker readiness, and unrelated workspace changes

  = must: treat this frame as current visible attention state
  = must: return clock_state, proof_state, balance_state, drive_state, next_step, and outside to CurrentFocalPoint when this focus pass closes
  = should: open child frames only when a concrete benchmark, scoring, or worker-profile pass is needed

(current_attention_runtime_registry_state) :active_root_frame: /semantic_register_set and return_anchor/ |registry_outside|
  + [active_root_frame] is attention_frame_2026_06_24_pressure_impact_pilot_candidate
  + [semantic_register_set] is focus, question, delineation, periphery, operation, evidence, Wisdom, Caution, balance, and integration registers
  + [return_anchor] is CurrentFocalPoint
  |registry_outside| hidden model state, executable runtime stack, unreviewed worker authority, unrelated dirty files, and untracked cognition

